[2] Cholera - Uganda (Masindi District)
Date: Fri, 17 Feb 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Monitor Online [edited]
<http://www.monitor.co.ug/news/reg02177.php>

13 people have been admitted at Buliisa Health Center in Masindi
district following a fresh cholera outbreak. The District Health
Inspector, Mr Patrick Baguma, told journalists at his office on Tue,
14 Feb 2006, that the outbreak had been reported in Buliisa County,
along the shores of Lake Albert. This comes 2 months after the
ministry of health declared the area free of the disease.
The disease was last reported in the district in Dec 2005. In 2005,
12 people died between Jul and Dec 2005.
Baguma said they had dispatched a team of medical experts from the
district headquarters to Buliisa to boost manpower in the area. No
deaths have been recorded so far.
He advised the people in the area to drink boiled water, avoid eating
cold food and construct toilets among other measures to control the
spread of the disease.
[Byline: Stephen Kabindi]
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
