[6] Cholera - Cameroon (South)
Date: Wed, 15 Feb 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: TodayOnline.com [edited]
<http://www.todayonline.com/articles/101260.asp>
8 people have died in the last 2 weeks in a cholera outbreak in
southern Cameroon and another 23 have been infected, the country's
health ministry said. The deaths and illnesses have been reported
around the town of Akonolinga, 140 kilometers (about 85 miles) east
of the capital Yaounde.
According to the ministry the disease spread after the body of
someone who had died at Douala, the economic capital of Cameroon, was
transferred to Akonolinga.
"It is an community-type epidemic that has killed 8 people because
they were in contact with the body, but it should be noted that those
who went to health centers were all saved," Dr Emmanuel Ngapana of
the national epidemological committee said.
From Jan 2004 to Apr 2005 more than 8500 cases of cholera were
registered in Cameroon, and 174 deaths were recorded.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
