[7] Diarrhea - Myanmar (Arakan State)
Date: Tue, 14 Feb 2006
From: Nita Madhav <nmadhav@alum.emory.edu>
Source: Narinjara News [edited]
<http://www.narinjara.com/details.asp?id=507>

There has been an outbreak of diarrhea in a village in the north of
Arakan State and 69 people are suffering critically from the disease,
said a source. The disease outbreak was in the village of Wrat Nyo
Daung under Buthidaung Township, on 11 Feb 2006.
10 people were sent to Buthidaung Township hospital immediately due
to severe symptoms. The remaining diarrhea-affected individuals were
given treatment by a medical team in the village.
In Wrat Nyo Daung Village, there are 187 households and 237 families
but only 20 toilets in the village. Due to inadequate toilet
facilities in the village the diarrhea spread quickly, said a health
worker from Buthidaung.
--
Nita Madhav, MSPH
Research Analyst
AIR Worldwide
Boston, MA, USA
<nmadhav@alum.emory.edu>
[The etiology (etiologies?) of this outbreak of diarrhea is not
clear, but cholera must be considered. Cholera was reported in a prison in
Arakan State earlier in 2006 -- see ref. (03) below. - Mods.LL,JW]
